 NACCIMA President, Iyalode Alaba Lawson  Congratulating the leadership of the Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs (NSCIA) and Nigerian Muslims, Aliyu prayed God to answer all prayers offered during Ramadan for peace, unity, economic growth and progress. She further called on Muslims to join other Nigerians and people of other faiths to continue to pray and work together for the promotion of peace, unity and love in the country. Tasking newly elected leaders to settle down to governance, she called on all elected leaders to embrace fairness, equity and justice in all their appointments and pursuit of economic growth and development.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .